<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1901-03-20T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1901-03-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="253" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d253">
                    <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Rockhill</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1901-03-20"><hi rend="italic">March 20,
                            1901</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                    <p>(Mr. Rockhill asks Mr. Hay’s opinion as to the questions involved in articles
                        8 and 9 of the Joint Note (Dismantling of forts and military occupation of
                        the road to the sea). Should these questions be discussed by the military
                        representatives of powers having troops in China alone, or also by those
                        which may take part in the application of military measures provided for by
                        said articles?)</p>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>